[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] The recursive least squares (RLS) algorithm considers an online approach to the least squares problem.
[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] One can look at RLS also in the context of adaptive filters (see RLS).
[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] The complexity for n steps of this algorithm is $O(nd^{2})$ , which is an order of magnitude faster than the corresponding batch learning complexity.
