[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] Then, it's easy to show that the same algorithm works with $\Gamma _{0}=(I+\lambda I)^{-1}$ , and the iterations proceed to give $\Gamma _{i}=(\Sigma _{i}+\lambda I)^{-1}$ .
