[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] However, the stepsize $\gamma _{i}$ needs to be chosen carefully to solve the expected risk minimization problem, as detailed above.
[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] By choosing a decaying step size $\gamma _{i}\approx {\frac {1}{\sqrt {i}}},$ one can prove the convergence of the average iterate ${\textstyle {\overline {w}}_{n}={\frac {1}{n}}\sum _{i=1}^{n}w_{i}}$ .
[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] This setting is a special case of stochastic optimization, a well known problem in optimization.
[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] In practice, one can perform multiple stochastic gradient passes (also called cycles or epochs) over the data.
