[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] The incremental gradient method can be shown to provide a minimizer to the empirical risk.
[src:online-learning-theory/online-machine-learning] Incremental techniques can be advantageous when considering objective functions made up of a sum of many terms e.g. an empirical error corresponding to a very large dataset.
